      "Electronic Drilling Recorder data reviewed"
    ],
    "summary": "On May 25, 2023, at 1:15am, approximately 79 barrels of zinc bromide brine was inadvertently discharged from a wellhead casing valve at Well Number C007 on Platform C at East Cameron Block 71. During BOP testing operations, a Floorhand was assigned to close a 1 13/16-inch 10M gate valve on the wellhead casing. The Floorhand believed the valve was closed but it was not fully closed. When zinc bromide brine was pumped to refill the production casing and BOP, the partially open valve allowed fluid to discharge into the Gulf of Mexico. The Floorhand noticed slower than normal returns and was sent to recheck the valve, where he fully closed it and stopped the flow. Investigation using Pit Volume Totalizer data determined the actual release was 79 barrels, significantly more than the initially reported 28 barrels.",
